(102, 1, '2018-09-21 15:09:55', '2018-09-21 18:09:55', '<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-100 alignleft\" src=\"http://localhost/ccbeu/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/june-party-pics-_2-300x221-300x221.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"221\" />A the time of the colonization of Brazil, in the 1500´s, the Portuguese implanted many European customs.  Two of which being state fairs or popular religious parties. But the emergence of such parties or fairs was during the pre-Gregorian period,  as a pagan festival in commemoration  of the great fertility of the earth and for the good harvest at that time called the summer solstice.  These celebrations also took place on June 24<sup>th</sup> Saint John´s day. These parties were known as, “ Joaninas”  and were named in honor of John the Baptist, who baptized people with water to prepare them for the coming of Jesus.  For this the celebration became part of the catholic church. Other saints are honored in this festival starting with Saint Anthony, June 13<sup>th</sup> ,  Saint John, June 24<sup>th</sup> , and Saint Peter June 29<sup>th</sup>. At these June parties people do a popular dance known as , “quadrilha”.  In this dance a fake wedding ceremony takes place, with the guests arriving in their best hillbilly clothes.  (straw hats, plaid shirts, and fancy patched dresses)  There is a priest who blesses the married couple and everyone takes the road home. There is a special choreography with guests finding broken bridges, snakes and the occasional shower of rain. One of the best parts of June parties is the food. As the celebration has to do with the harvest and fertility of the land most of the food served is made from corn. There are cakes, pastries corn on the cob, and of course not to forget the “bolinho caipira”. There are various recipes to  on how to make these “bolinhos” but again the essential ingredient is the corn flour.  The flour can be mixed with ground beef, jerked beef  and herbs then fried. The typical drinks are mulled wine or quentão.  <sup>  </sup>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nFESTAS JUNINAS\r\n\r\nNa época da colonização do Brasil, em 1500, os portugueses implantaram muitos costumes europeus. Dois deles festas nacionais e religiosas. Mas o surgimento de tais festas é do período Pré-Gregoriano, como uma festa pagã em comemoração a fertilidade da terra e a boa colheita naquela época chamada de solstício de verão. Estas comemorações aconteciam também em 24 de junho, dia de Santo Antônio. Estas festas eram conhecidas como “Joaninas” e chamadas assim em honra a João Batista, que batizava pessoas com água para prepará-los para a vinda de Jesus. Esta celebração tornou-se parte da igreja católica. Outros santos são homenageados neste festival começando por Santo Antônio, 13 de junho, São João, 24 de junho, e São Pedro em 29 de junho. Nas festas juninas as pessoas realizam uma dança popular conhecida como “quadrilha”. Nesta dança uma casamento falso acontece, os convidados vestem suas melhores roupas caipiras (chapéu de palha, camisa xadrez, e vestidos remendados e enfeitados). Há um padre que abençoa o casal e todos pegam a estrada para casa. Há uma coreografia especial que os convidados encontram pontes quebradas, cobras e chuva no percurso. Uma das melhores partes da festa é a comida. Como a festa tem a ver com colheita e fertilidade da terra a maioria da comida é feita com milho. Há bolos, milho verde na espiga, e claro o “bolinho caipira”. Há várias receitas de como fazer bolinhos, mas o ingrediente essencial é a farinha de milho. A farinha pode ser misturada a carne moída, carne seca e ervas e depois é frito. As bebidas típicas são vinho quente ou quentão.\r\n\r\nTexto sobre festa junina por Edna de Souza, Marina Oliveira e Larissa Portes.', 'JUNE PARTIES', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '99-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-09-21 15:09:55', '2018-09-21 18:09:55', '', 99, 'http://localhost/ccbeu/2018/09/21/99-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(103, 1, '2015-06-30 15:10:18', '2015-06-30 18:10:18', 'Every year, we throw more and more trash in places that are not appropriate. We are quickly running out of space. That is why it is very important to learn the three R\'s of the environment: REDUCE, REUSE and RECYCLE. We can do this every day, by not buying things you don\'t need or items that cannot be recycled. Now, let’s learn more about these 3 powerful words with the students of “World Class 1” : Victor Hugo, Vitor Fori and Giullya Becker!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ccbeucaraguatatuba.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/3-rs-pic-1.jpg\"><img class=\" size-medium wp-image-369 alignleft\" src=\"http://ccbeucaraguatatuba.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/3-rs-pic-1.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"3 Rs Pic 1\" width=\"300\" height=\"228\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong> REDUCE</strong>\r\n\r\nWhy should we reduce? How should we reduce? How will reducing help us and the nature? What should we reduce? Will Reducing harm us?\r\n\r\nWhen you waste a lot of paper, water, energy or plastic, for example, it isn\'t only your money that is being wasted, the trees are dying, the rivers are running out of water, the plastic can kill animals etc.\r\n\r\nBut how do we reduce? Reducing is really simple and it is something that all of us can do! For example: after you eat your breakfast and brush your teeth, if you leave the tap open you will use more water than you should, and you won\'t damage only the environment but also yourself, even paying more on your bills. Another example is how much money you spend buying things you don’t even need, like when you have an iPhone 4 working perfectly but you tell yourself that you need an iPhone 6. Do you really need it? Or is it just the consumer habit that makes you want more and more things? So, by quitting this habit, you will reduce lots of things like buying a new notebook when you already have one with just one page used; or having less electronic products (cell phones, laptop computers, tablets) and reducing the power to charge them. By reducing those things, you won’t waste nature resources and money.\r\n\r\nAlmost everyone says more is better than less, and I can say that is almost true because it is good to have more money but is better to have less debt in life and have a clear conscience for not having damaged our environment.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ccbeucaraguatatuba.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/recycle-pic-2.gif\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-372\" src=\"http://ccbeucaraguatatuba.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/recycle-pic-2.gif\" alt=\"Recycle Pic 2\" width=\"285\" height=\"266\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>REUSE</strong>\r\n\r\n“Before you throw away those used cans, <em>or anything else for that matter, check to see if you can reuse it.” [ </em>Source: <a href=\"http://www.motherearthnews.com/\">http://www.motherearthnews.com/</a>]\r\nWhat does REUSE mean?\r\n\r\n<em>“Reuse is very different from recycling.  Instead of carefully discarding items that can be recycled to make new products, reuse involves using the items in another way, when their primary use is finished.”</em> [ Source:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.reuserecycle.net/what-is-reuse.php\">http://www.reuserecycle.net/what-is-reuse.php</a> ]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nReuse is basically making new things after its primary use has finished. For example: you can use a glass bottle as a vase instead of throwing it away and damaging the nature. The difference between recycling and reuse is when you recycle you use an industrial process, and when you reuse, you change the role of the object. This is very important because you don’t burn anything and help the nature by not releasing greenhouse gases.\r\n\r\n<strong>RECYCLE</strong>\r\n\r\n<em>“Recycling is the process of making or manufacturing new products from a product that has originally served its purpose.”</em> [ Source: <a href=\"http://www.benefits-of-recycling.com/whatisrecycling/\">http://www.benefits-of-recycling.com/whatisrecycling/</a> ]\r\n\r\n<em>“Recyclable materials include many kinds of glass, paper, metal, plastic, textiles, and electronics. […] Another form of recycling is the salvage of certain materials from complex products, either due to their intrinsic value (e.g., lead from car batteries, or gold from computer components), or due to their hazardous nature (e.g., removal and reuse of mercury from various items).”</em> [ Source: <a href=\"http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recycling\">http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recycling</a> ]\r\n\r\nRecycling is very important for the nature and for you too. Instead of throwing things away, you can recycle them, because if you throw them in the trash, it would take a long time to decompose. There are 5 appropriate trash cans for: paper, glass, metal, plastic and organic. And it isn’t just the plain paper we have lots of types of paper, for example: paper card, cardboard, newsprint and many others. For glass, I can name bottles, mirrors, dishes and home decorations. For metal we have cans and wires; and for plastic, bags, earphones, packages, food packaging, clothing buttons and bottles. The organic is the food that is left. We can do composting which helps plants to grow better and stay healthy.\r\n\r\nWith the process of recycling we can reduce the thash in inappropriate places and this is very important for the environment. We can get an old booklet and take it to a recycling place and after the industrial process, we will have a new booklet. With that action, we save a lot of trees. If we recycle, we will be the difference and by our example, we can change minds so that they will also make a difference. Let’s go!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ccbeucaraguatatuba.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/recycle-pic-1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-370 size-medium\" src=\"http://ccbeucaraguatatuba.com.br/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/recycle-pic-1.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"Recycle Pic 1\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\r\n\r\n**Recycle Pic 1 – yellow (metal) ; green (glass) ; blue (paper) ; red (plastic) ; brown/gray (organic)\r\n\r\n[gallery columns=\"1\" size=\"medium\" type=\"slideshow\" ids=\"378,377,376,375,371\" orderby=\"rand\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Os 3 Rs</strong>\r\n\r\nTodo ano nós jogamos mais e mais lixo em lugares inapropriados. Rapidamente ficaremos sem espaço. Esta é  a importância de aprendermos os 3 Rs do meio ambiente: REDUZA, REUSE e RECICLE. Podemos fazer isso diáriamente, não comprando coisas que não precisamos ou itens que não podem ser reciclados. Agora vamos aprender mais sobre essas 3 poderosas palavras com alunos do World Class 1: Victor Hugo, Vitor Fori e Giullya Becker!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>REDUZA</strong>\r\n\r\nPor que devemos reduzir? Como podemos reduzir? Como a redução poderá ajudar a natureza? O que devemos reduzir? A redução nos prejudicará?\r\n\r\nQuando você gasta muito papel, água, energia ou plástico, por exemplo, não é apenas o seu dinheiro que é gasto, árvores estão morrendo, rios secando, e o plástico matando animais e etc.\r\n\r\nMas como reduzir? Reduzir é muito simples e é algo que todos podemos fazer! Por exemplo: depois do café você escova os dentes, se você deixar a torneira aberta você gastará mais água do que deveria e não prejudique só o ambiente, mas também você mesmo, pagando mais por suas contas. Outro exemplo é quanto dinheiro você gasta comprando coisas que você nem precise, como quando você tem um iPhone 4 em perfeito estado, mas diz a você mesmo que precisa de um iPhone 6. Realmente precisa? Ou é apenas o hábito do consume que o faz querer mais coisas? Então eliminando este hábito você reduzirá muito, como comprar um caderno novo quando já tem um com uma página usada; ou possuindo menos produtos eletrônicos (celulares, computadores, tablets) e causando uma queda de preços. Reduzindo você não desperdiçará recursos naturais nem dinheiro.\r\n\r\nAs pessoas dizem que mais é melhor que menos, e eu digo que é quase uma verdade porque é melhor ter mais dinheiro, mas ter menos dívidas na vida e ter a consciência limpa de não ter prejudicado nosso meio ambiente.', 'The 3 R’s', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-3-rs', '', '', '2018-09-21 15:12:16', '2018-09-21 18:12:16', '', 0, 'http://localhost/ccbeu/?p=103', 0, 'post', '', 0),
